claim.claim-text:
A control unit (200) for authorizing a single use medical imaging device comprising:
a connector (128) for connecting the control unit to the single use medical imaging device;
a device interface (210) capable of receiving a code in a format of an image signal produced by the medical imaging device, wherein the code encodes an identifier uniquely associated with the imaging device;
a processor (230) that decodes the identifier from the image signal; and
means (230, 252) for determining if the single use imaging device is authorized based upon the identifier associated with the device,
wherein the code is embedded in an image of a verification object and the verification object further comprises one or more patterns to calibrate or functionally test the single use imaging device.

A medical imaging system (100) comprising:
a control unit according to claim 1 or claim 2; and
a single use medical imaging device (120), having a shaft (123) with a proximal end (124) and a distal end (122);
a connector (128) on the proximal end for connecting the device to the control unit (200);
an image sensor (150) at or adjacent to the distal end (122) for producing images in a predefined format for receipt by an imaging board (264) within the control unit (200);
an image of the verification object (400) encoding the identifier uniquely associated with the device;
a transmit circuit (152) that transmits the image of the verification object (400) to the control unit in the predefined format of the image signals produced by the image sensor.

A method of automatically authorizing and self-testing a medical device (120) containing an image element comprising the steps of:
recognizing the medical device as authorized based upon electronic detection of an image of a prerecorded verification object;
automatically calibrating the device using calibrating features included in the verification object;
functionally testing the device; and
activating the device upon successful authorization, calibration and functional testing.

A method for authorizing a single use imaging device (120) comprising:
connecting the single use imaging device to a control unit (200);
electronically obtaining (620) an image of a prerecorded verification object (400) associated with the imaging device wherein the verification object image encodes an identifier and a set of calibration objects;
extracting (630) the identifier from the image of the verification object; and
authorizing (650) the use of the imaging device by comparing the identifier to a database (258) containing information on authorized identifiers, wherein a match between the identifier and information in the database results in authorization (670) for use.

A method of serializing a set of single use imaging devices comprising:
assigning a unique serial identifier to each imaging device to be manufactured;
encoding the serial identifier in a verification object, wherein the verification object also includes a set of calibration objects;
associating the verification object with each corresponding imaging device at the time of manufacture; and
maintaining a registry of authorized serial identifiers corresponding to manufactured serialized imaging devices wherein a user of an imaging device may determine if the device is authorized by comparing the serial identifier to the database.
